definition: ordinal number/day of a month/mark/sign/business establishment/size/ship suffix/horn (wind instrument)/bugle call/assumed name/to take a pulse/classifier used to indicate number of people

sentences.english: The commonest words are starred in this dictionary.
sentences.chinese: 在本詞典中，最常用的單詞前加有星號。

sentences.english: Required properties will have an asterisk next to them.
sentences.chinese: 必要屬性旁邊有一個星號。

sentences.english: In the list the starred questions are the most difficult.
sentences.chinese: 在這張表裏，加星號的問題是最難的。

sentences.english: The asterisk refers the reader to a footnote.
sentences.chinese: 星號指引讀者去查閱腳註。

sentences.english: The question mark and asterisk can be used more than once in the same profile.
sentences.chinese: 可以在相同配置文件中使用多個問號和星號。

sentences.english: For example, you may surround the text with parentheses or asterisks.
sentences.chinese: 例如，您可以用括號或星號括住文本。

sentences.english: The asterisked questions may be omitted.
sentences.chinese: 帶星號的問題可以略去。

sentences.english: Where a star, the star, means pure water.
The personality ended at star one.
Indicates that an object's text representation is obscured by characters such as asterisks.
sentences.chinese: 代表物件的文字表示由星號之類的字元所遮蔽。

sentences.english: Mandatory parameters are marked with an asterisk in the first table column.
sentences.chinese: 必需參數在該表的第一列中標上了星號。

sentences.english: Items with asterisk exceed a conservative lower limit for vibration-free design.
sentences.chinese: 帶有星號標誌的項目超出了無振動設計的保守下限。

sentences.english: The asterisk refers to a footnote.
Star one says death occurs when personality stops functioning.
sentences.chinese: 星號一說，死亡在人格功能停止時發生。

sentences.english: The starred dishes on the menu are suitable for vegetarians.
sentences.chinese: 菜單上標有星號的菜最宜素食者選用。
